epigram_english:
Nature teaches Nature how to conquer fire;
The teacher and the pupil are of the same kind.
A woman is taught by another woman to wash clothes;
The skilled one leads the unskilled.
Nature teaches, Nature conquers, Nature rules:
All wisdom comes from following her.

Three things are sufficient for mastery:
White smoke, that is water;
The green Lion, that is the Ore of Hermes;
And stinking water.
With these three, rightly combined,
The Work may be brought to completion.

Listen to the screech owl's voice,
Which it produces itself, and the water.
Do not heed any bird that cries in the evening;
For the owl alone speaks truth in the darkness.
The philosophical mercury is nocturnal;
Only by night-wisdom is the Stone found.

Sol and his shadow complete the work.
Two stones are given, one manifest, one hidden;
The visible and invisible aspects of a single substance.
Neglect neither the light nor the dark;
Both are needed for the final projection,
When the stone achieves its full power.
